# osshp Caddyfile
#
# Caddy terminates TLS in-stack (the DEFAULT, "direct" deployment mode).
# For a real domain, Caddy automatically obtains a Let's Encrypt certificate
# (ports 80 + 443 must be reachable). For local dev
# (OSSHP_DOMAIN=localhost), Caddy uses its internal CA.
#
# The site address is {$OSSHP_CADDY_SITE_ADDRESS}, injected by
# docker-compose.yml. It DEFAULTS to {$OSSHP_DOMAIN} (a bare domain), so
# direct mode is unchanged: Caddy sees the bare domain and does auto-HTTPS.
#
# In Cloudflare Tunnel mode (docker-compose.tunnel.yml overlay), setup.sh
# sets OSSHP_CADDY_SITE_ADDRESS=http://<domain> in .env. The leading
# `http://` tells Caddy to serve plain HTTP on :80 and NOT attempt a
# certificate — TLS is terminated at Cloudflare's edge and cloudflared
# reaches this proxy over the internal Docker network. OSSHP_DOMAIN /
# OSSHP_RP_ID stay bare and OSSHP_ORIGIN stays https://<domain>, so
# WebAuthn + Secure cookies are unaffected.

{$OSSHP_CADDY_SITE_ADDRESS} {
    reverse_proxy app:3000
}
